@node "Bug reports"

If you have found a bug in this program, please send me a letter with a
description of the bug, when it occurs, which set-up you are using, which
version if AGIndex and the system software (especially @{"AmigaGuide" link AmigaGuide}
and @{"amigaguide.library" link "amigaguide.library"}) you are using etcetera.

Also if you have suggestions for improvements or additions that should be
made you can also write.

If you want to write, write to the following address:

   Camiel Rouweler
   Oranjestraat 9
   5611 JG Eindhoven
   the Netherlands


I also like fanmail, so even if you do not have a good reason to write,
then just write that you like using AGIndex!
@endnode


@node AmigaGuide
AmigaGuide is the standard Commodore help read utility. Documents (like
this guide) can be read and by using references to other parts in the text,
the user can quickly find the information or help she/he needs. Also
on-line help in a number of programs is possible.

AmigaGuide comes with the Workbench 3.0 disks (included in the utility
'MultiView') and with a growing number of commercial programs. If you do
not have a copy of AmigaGuide, you can find the currently most recent
version on AmigaLibDisk (fred Fish) 920.

There are two different versions: one for OS1.3 and OS2.0 and one for
OS3.0; both are present on said disk.
@endnode


@node "amigaguide.library"
The amigaguide.library is a library used by the AmigaGuide utility. This
library MUST be installed in your libs: drawer in order to run AmigaGuide
or MultiView. But you probably would not be reading this if it was not
installed!
@endnode

@NODE INDEXNODE "Index"
This is the kind of index that AGIndex creates. Of course for small
documents like this one, it is rather silly to have an index, but if I had
no index in this guide, I would not be promoting AGIndex really well,
would I?

